{"id":348801,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peep_Show_(TV_series)","text":"\"Peep Show\" is a British television sitcom starring David Mitchell and Robert Webb. It ran from 19 September 2003 - 16 December 2015. It was created by Andrew O'Connor, Jesse Armstrong and Sam Bain. It was written by Armstrong, Bain and Simon Blackwell. Mitchell won a BAFTA Award for his role.\nMitchell plays Mark Corrigan, Webb plays Jeremy Usborne. They are two young men who share a flat in Croydon, London. They are friends despite being very different to each other. Much of the show's humour is about the difference between the two central characters.\nMark is conservative, studious, intelligent, hard-working, frugal, socially awkward and loves history. He is a loan manager for the first five series.\nJeremy is unemployed, irresponsible, dishonest, lazy, promiscuous bisexual and hedonistic. From series 1 - 7 he attempts to become a professional musician. In series 8 and 9 he is a life coach.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"United_Kingdom","surface_form":"British","offset":17},{"uri":"Television","surface_form":"television","offset":25},{"uri":"Sitcom","surface_form":"sitcom","offset":36},{"uri":"David_Mitchell","surface_form":"David Mitchell","offset":52},{"uri":"Robert_Webb","surface_form":"Robert Webb","offset":71},{"uri":"Creation","surface_form":"created","offset":141},{"uri":"Andrew_O%27Connor_(actor)","surface_form":"Andrew O'Connor","offset":152},{"uri":"Jesse_Armstrong","surface_form":"Jesse Armstrong","offset":169},{"uri":"Sam_Bain","surface_form":"Sam Bain","offset":189},{"uri":"Simon_Blackwell","surface_form":"Simon Blackwell","offset":237},{"uri":"BAFTA","surface_form":"BAFTA","offset":269},{"uri":"Award","surface_form":"Award","offset":275},{"uri":"Role","surface_form":"role","offset":289},{"uri":"Men","surface_form":"men","offset":371},{"uri":"Apartment","surface_form":"flat","offset":387},{"uri":"Croydon","surface_form":"Croydon","offset":395